.TH "snd_usb_endpoint_stop" 9 "snd_usb_endpoint_stop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_usb_endpoint_stop \- stop an snd_usb_endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_usb_endpoint_stop
.BI "(struct snd_usb_endpoint *ep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
the endpoint to stop (may be NULL)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A call to this function will decrement the running count of the endpoint.
In case the last user has requested the endpoint stop, the URBs will
actually be deactivated.

Must be balanced to calls of \fBsnd_usb_endpoint_start\fP.

The caller needs to synchronize the pending stop operation via
\fBsnd_usb_endpoint_sync_pending_stop\fP.
